# MazeLedger Bot Trading API

Build trading bots that place **spot (INR)** and **futures (USDT-M)** orders on ZebPay. You write the
bot logic + UI; MazeLedger handles execution, risk caps, idempotency, audit, and a sandbox. Each
end-user brings their **own ZebPay keys (BYO)** — no custody.

Base URL `https://mazeledger.ai` · Auth header `x-api-key` (`ml_test_…` sandbox or `ml_live_…` live).

The `mazeledger-bots` MCP server (configured in `.cursor/mcp.json`) exposes tools: `list_symbols`,
`get_account`, `get_positions`, `place_futures_order`, `close_position`. Sandbox keys simulate; live
keys place real orders.

## Get a key (one-time)
```
POST /api/v1/onboarding/organizations { "name": "Acme", "country": "IN" }   -> sandbox key (once)
POST /api/v1/organizations/{id}/exchange-connections { "apiKey": "...", "apiSecret": "..." }
POST /api/v1/organizations/{id}/risk-acknowledgment { "acknowledge": true }
POST /api/v1/organizations/{id}/api-keys { "mode": "live" }                  -> live key
```
Set the key as the `MAZELEDGER_API_KEY` env var (referenced by `.cursor/mcp.json`).

## End-users (multi-user bots)
`POST /api/v1/users { externalUserId, apiKey, apiSecret }` then pass `endUserId` on trading calls.
`GET /api/v1/users` · `GET/DELETE /api/v1/users/{externalUserId}`.

## Futures (USDT-M)
```
POST /api/v1/futures/orders { endUserId?, symbol:"DOGEUSDT", side:"BUY", type:"MARKET",
  notionalUsd|quantity, leverage, clientOrderId }
GET  /api/v1/futures/orders/{id} · GET /api/v1/futures/positions?endUserId=
POST /api/v1/futures/positions/{id}/close?endUserId= · GET /api/v1/futures/account?endUserId=
GET  /api/v1/exchange/symbols?symbol=DOGEUSDT
```

## Spot (INR; ₹99 minimum)
```
POST /api/v1/spot/orders { endUserId?, symbol:"BTC", side:"buy", amountInr }      // market buy
POST /api/v1/spot/orders { symbol:"BTC", side:"sell", quantity }                  // market sell
GET  /api/v1/spot/orders/{id} · GET /api/v1/spot/account
```

## Reporting
`GET /api/v1/orders?externalUserId=&status=&limit=` · `GET /api/v1/users/{externalUserId}/orders` ·
`GET /api/v1/stats` (users, orders total/today, by status, by market).

## Building a bot
A bot = your logic calling these on a schedule/signal: decide → size (`list_symbols`/`get_account`)
→ place with a stable `clientOrderId` (idempotent) → track (`get_positions`/`/orders`) → `close_position`.
Ideas: DCA, grid, TP/SL manager, copy-trading.

## Safety
Sandbox first. Risk caps per org (order size, leverage, daily notional, open positions) + exchange
minimums → `422 RISK_CAP_REJECTED`. Idempotency via `clientOrderId`; ambiguous failures recorded
`unknown` (re-query before retry). BYO keys should be trade-only. Full docs: `https://mazeledger.ai/docs`.
